# <name> — Web UI runtime check

A runnable scaffold for a project-authored verification skill that drives the
**running web UI** in a real browser and asserts the user journey end-to-end.
Uses Chrome MCP directly, or delegates the visual pass to
`/dev-process-toolkit:visual-check` when a rubber-duck MCP is configured.

> Read the authoring guide — `docs/verification-skills.md` — before filling this
> in. It covers how `verify_skill` wires this into the `## Verification` hook and
> why the disable-model-invocation marker keeps the skill opt-in.

## What this checks

The real front-end journey rendered in a browser — routing, interaction, dynamic
content, and console health — which unit/component tests cannot observe.
Deterministic gates (typecheck, lint, `test`) run first and always win; this
check adds the runtime UI behavior on top.

